# Prisma Schema Conventions

## Model Pattern
```prisma
model FeatureEntry {
  id        String   @id @default(auto()) @map("_id") @db.ObjectId
  // ... fields
  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt
  @@map("feature_entry")
}
```

## Key Rules
- All models use `@id @default(auto()) @map("_id") @db.ObjectId` for MongoDB
- Collection names are snake_case via `@@map()`
- Always include `createdAt` and `updatedAt`
- Token-based ownership: `ownerToken String?`
- Auth-based ownership: `userId String @db.ObjectId` with `user User @relation(...)` 
- Image fields: `imageUrl String` + `imagePublicId String` (or arrays for multi-image)
- After schema changes: stop dev server, run `npx prisma generate` then `npx prisma db push`

## Existing Models
- **Auth**: User (with `isAdmin`, `isBugAdmin`, `isAboutAdmin`, `badges String[]`), Session, Account, Verification
- **Content**: Post, PostImage, Comment, GalleryImage, GuestbookEntry, Adventure
- **Tasks**: Todo (with `assignedToId`, `completedById`, `recurring`, `status`)
- **Expenses**: Expense, ExpenseComment, ExpenseVote
- **Nature**: LoonObservation (with arrays: `loonIds`, `behaviors`, `imageUrls`, `imagePublicIds`)
- **Puzzles**: PuzzleEntry (with `completedBy`, `completedDate`, `pieceCount`)
- **System**: Feedback, SiteSetting
